  "description": "Improving the UV-yeast experiment with sterile technique.",
  "body_html": "<p><em>Thanks to <a href=\"https://notes.livingphysics.org/\">David Jordan at Living Physics </a>for the support. All mistakes are mine.</em> </p><p>In my last post, <a href=\"https://chillphysicsenjoyer.substack.com/p/results-from-blasting-yeast-with\">I measured the effect of UV on yeast</a>. But when I grew the solution on agar plates, they got contaminated. </p><p>So, I tried again. This time with <strong>sterile technique</strong>. </p><p>I made a 70% ethanol solution, and ran it through the pump to kill any contaminants before each run. </p><p>When the pump was in action and taking solution out of the tube, I lighted an ethanol lamp to create an updraft of air. This updraft prevents contaminants from getting in the tube, since its open. It\u2019s cheaper than a Bunsen burner. </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!jo5B!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2998d8eb-e07d-46c4-850c-1b6d6cb231fc_666x370.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!jo5B!,w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2998d8eb-e07d-46c4-850c-1b6d6cb231fc_666x370.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!jo5B!,w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2998d8eb-e07d-46c4-850c-1b6d6cb231fc_666x370.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!jo5B!,w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2998d8eb-e07d-46c4-850c-1b6d6cb231fc_666x370.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!jo5B!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2998d8eb-e07d-46c4-850c-1b6d6cb231fc_666x370.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!jo5B!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2998d8eb-e07d-46c4-850c-1b6d6cb231fc_666x370.png\" width=\"666\" height=\"370\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2998d8eb-e07d-46c4-850c-1b6d6cb231fc_666x370.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:370,&quot;width&quot;:666,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:493384,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://chillphysicsenjoyer.substack.com/i/178531543?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2998d8eb-e07d-46c4-850c-1b6d6cb231fc_666x370.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!jo5B!,w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2998d8eb-e07d-46c4-850c-1b6d6cb231fc_666x370.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!jo5B!,w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2998d8eb-e07d-46c4-850c-1b6d6cb231fc_666x370.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!jo5B!,w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2998d8eb-e07d-46c4-850c-1b6d6cb231fc_666x370.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!jo5B!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2998d8eb-e07d-46c4-850c-1b6d6cb231fc_666x370.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\"><svg role=\"img\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>After running the yeast through UV, and before plating the solution, I first dipped a glass rod in pure ethanol. Then put it in the flame. I waved the rod in the air for a few seconds to cool it. Then I dipped it in the treated yeast solution and spread it on the plate. </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\">